To produce a new openjpeg release (Win32, Linux or OSX):

1. Generate the CHANGES for the release:

$ ./genchange.sh

copy the branch

$ svn copy https://openjpeg.googlecode.com/svn/branches/openjpeg-1.5 https://openjpeg.googlecode.com/svn/tags/version.1.5
$ svn add CHANGES ../../tags/version.1.5
$ svn commit

2. Generates the source tarball + binary tarball (OSX package on Mac):

$ ./release.sh

If you have a windows box, from a CMD console:

> release.bat

You can use googlecode_upload.py to upload your files directly:

# LINUX:
$ ./googlecode_upload.py -s "Version 1.5 source files of OpenJPEG library and codecs" -p openjpeg -l Featured,OpSys-All,Type-Source /tmp/openjpeg_release/openjpeg-build/openjpeg-1.5.0.tar.gz
$ ./googlecode_upload.py -s "Version 1.5 Linux Binaries of OpenJPEG library and codecs" -p openjpeg -l Featured,OpSys-Linux,Type-Executable /tmp/openjpeg_release/openjpeg-build/OPENJPEG-1.5.0-Linux.tar.gz

# MACOSX (10.4/ppc)
$ ./googlecode_upload.py -s "Version 1.5 MacOSX (Tiger/10.4) Binaries of OpenJPEG library and codecs" -p openjpeg -l Featured,OpSys-OSX,Type-Executable /tmp/openjpeg_release/openjpeg-build/openjpeg-1.5.0-Darwin-powerpc.dmg

